parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or will not start
the key falls out of the ignition switch
the ignition switch feels stuck or worn out
the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle's systems to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical systems
such as the headlights
radio
and door locks
malfunction or fail to work
the vehicle's warning lights illuminate
the vehicle stalls or will not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Turn Signal and Hazard Light Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turn signal and hazard lights can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's intentions.
symptoms: The turn signals and hazard lights malfunction or fail to work
the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag system malfunctions or fails to deploy
the vehicle's electrical system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without warning
the accelerator pedal sticks
the vehicle fails to stop when the brake pedal is depressed
the engine revs up excessively
and the vehicle may continue to accelerate even after the driver removes their foot from the accelerator pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck
the pedal does not return to its normal position
the engine revs up excessively
and the vehicle may accelerate without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the vehicle speed control system can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without warning
the accelerator pedal sticks
the vehicle fails to stop when the brake pedal is depressed
and the engine revs up excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
the ignition switch does not turn on
the key does not turn in the ignition
the vehicle shuts off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel is difficult to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel has a lot of play
the tie rod breaks
the rack and pinion bracket breaks
the steering wheel falls apart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
the ABS light and security light come on
the radio turns off
the vehicle is difficult to start or jump-start.
